## Hi-Hat from Pure Noise

A hi-hat is just noise—multiple bandpass filters stacked, short envelope, high frequencies. No tone required.

```scheme
;; Hi-hat — stacked bandpass filters on white noise, tight envelope
(adsr (filter 'bandpass
              (filter 'bandpass
                      (noise 'white 0.2)
                      :cutoff 8000
                      :q 2.0)
              :cutoff 12000
              :q 1.5)
      :a 0.002
      :d 0.08
      :s 0.0
      :r 0.05)
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

---

## Layering Noise with Tone — The Snare Drum

A real snare drum has two parts: a **tone** (the drum head vibrating) and **noise** (the snares rattling). Layer them.

```scheme
;; Snare drum — tone + noise, same envelope
(let ((envelope (lambda (sound)
                  (adsr sound
                        :a 0.005
                        :d 0.12
                        :s 0.0
                        :r 0.08))))
  (list (envelope (tone 180 0.2))
        (envelope (filter 'bandpass
                          (noise 'white 0.2)
                          :cutoff 3000
                          :q 4.0))))
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

The tone gives the pitch (180 Hz, a low thud). The noise gives the rattle. Together: snare.

---

## Wind — Lowpass Noise with Slow Modulation

Wind isn't static—it gusts, fades, swirls. A slow envelope on lowpass noise creates the swell.

```scheme
;; Wind gust — lowpass pink noise, slow swell
(adsr (filter 'lowpass
              (noise 'pink 4.0)
              :cutoff 600
              :q 0.7)
      :a 1.0
      :d 2.0
      :s 0.3
      :r 1.0)
```

*[needs: noise-pink, filter-verbs, adsr-verb]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise-pink, filter-verbs, adsr-verb -->

---

## Ocean Waves — Layered Noise at Different Rates

Ocean waves are noise at multiple scales: low rumble (the wave body), mid hiss (foam), high shimmer (spray). Layer bandpass filters at different cutoffs.

```scheme
;; Ocean wave — three bandpass layers
(list (filter 'lowpass
              (noise 'pink 6.0)
              :cutoff 200
              :q 0.5)
      (filter 'bandpass
              (noise 'white 6.0)
              :cutoff 1200
              :q 1.0)
      (filter 'highpass
              (noise 'white 6.0)
              :cutoff 5000
              :q 0.8))
```

*[needs: noise-pink, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: noise-pink, filter-verbs -->

---

## Breath Layer — Adding Air to a Flute

A synthesized flute without breath sounds thin, digital. Add a **quiet layer** of highpass noise—just enough to hear the air moving.

```scheme
;; Flute with breath — tone + quiet highpass noise
(let ((flute-tone (wave 'sine 523 1.0))
      (breath (filter 'highpass
                      (noise 'white 1.0)
                      :cutoff 3000
                      :q 0.6)))
  (list flute-tone
        (list :gain 0.15 breath)))
```

*[needs: filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: filter-verbs, gain/mix verbs -->

The `:gain 0.15` keeps the breath quiet—too loud and it's all hiss, too quiet and you lose the texture.

---

## Bow Chatter — Noise Modulating a String Tone

When a bow drags across a string, it doesn't glide smoothly—it catches and releases, adding texture. Layer a **fast-attack noise burst** at the start of a bowed note.

```scheme
;; Bowed string with attack chatter
(let ((string-tone (wave 'saw 220 2.0))
      (bow-chatter (adsr (filter 'bandpass
                                 (noise 'white 0.1)
                                 :cutoff 1800
                                 :q 2.5)
                         :a 0.01
                         :d 0.08
                         :s 0.0
                         :r 0.02)))
  (list string-tone
        (list :gain 0.3 bow-chatter)))
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs, gain/mix -->

---

## Vocal Breath — Noise Before a Sung Note

Singers inhale before they sing. A short burst of lowpass noise before the tone models that breath.

```scheme
;; Sung note with inhale
(let ((breath (adsr (filter 'lowpass
                            (noise 'white 0.2)
                            :cutoff 1200
                            :q 0.8)
                    :a 0.05
                    :d 0.15
                    :s 0.0
                    :r 0.0))
      (sung-tone (adsr (tone 330 1.5)
                       :a 0.1
                       :d 0.3
                       :s 0.7
                       :r 0.4)))
  (list breath sung-tone))
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

