## Rain — Randomized Bursts of Filtered Noise

Rain is thousands of tiny impacts. Simulate it with **many short bursts** of bandpass noise at random intervals.

```scheme
;; Single raindrop — short noise burst
(adsr (filter 'bandpass
              (noise 'white 0.05)
              :cutoff 2400
              :q 1.2)
      :a 0.001
      :d 0.03
      :s 0.0
      :r 0.02)
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

A real rain texture needs scheduling (Chapter 11) to scatter the drops across time.

