## Fire Crackle — Sparse High-Q Bandpass Bursts

Fire crackles at unpredictable moments—narrow bandpass (high Q) bursts at varying frequencies.

```scheme
;; Fire pop — high-Q bandpass, short envelope
(adsr (filter 'bandpass
              (noise 'white 0.08)
              :cutoff 1600
              :q 8.0)
      :a 0.005
      :d 0.05
      :s 0.0
      :r 0.03)
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

Vary the cutoff frequency for each pop to break the pattern.

