## Tom-Tom — Low Tone with Short Noise Rattle

A tom-tom is a pitched drum (low tone, fast decay) with a brief noise rattle.

```scheme
;; Tom-tom
(let ((body (adsr (tone 120 0.6)
                  :a 0.01
                  :d 0.5
                  :s 0.0
                  :r 0.1))
      (rattle (adsr (filter 'bandpass
                            (noise 'white 0.15)
                            :cutoff 2000
                            :q 2.5)
                    :a 0.005
                    :d 0.1
                    :s 0.0
                    :r 0.05)))
  (list body
        (list :gain 0.2 rattle)))
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs, gain/mix -->

