## Reverse Cymbal Swell — Inverted Envelope on Noise

A reverse cymbal starts quiet and swells to loud—an inverted envelope.

```scheme
;; Reverse cymbal swell (inverted ADSR concept)
(adsr (filter 'highpass
              (noise 'white 3.0)
              :cutoff 6000
              :q 1.2)
      :a 2.5
      :d 0.0
      :s 1.0
      :r 0.5)
```

*[needs: adsr-verb, filter-verbs]*  
<!-- BUILD: adsr-verb, filter-verbs -->

The long attack creates the swell; sustain holds the peak before release.

